<item>
            <title>[LU-2925] OUT service of MDS needs bigger request buffer</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2925</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;this patch (&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4940&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4940&lt;/a&gt;) assumes that most MDS services only need 5K as request buffer size, the only exception is &quot;regular&quot; service which can get large request with LOV EA information. &lt;br/&gt;
However, OUT service of DNE can have request size up to 9K, which means we also need to define individual buffer size for OUT. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="17791">LU-2925</key>
            <summary>OUT service of MDS needs bigger request buffer</summary>
